  <h2>Using Presets</h2>

  <h3>Web UI</h3>
  <p>
    Presets are available from two entry points in the web UI:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>New Job</strong> — In the job creation form, select <em>Preset</em> as the pipeline type and choose a preset from the dropdown. Built-in presets appear first, followed by custom presets sorted alphabetically.</li>
    <li><strong>Presets Library</strong> — Navigate to <strong>Settings &gt; Presets</strong> to view, create, clone, edit, and delete presets. Each preset page shows the full FFmpeg argument list and a diff view when compared to the built-in it was cloned from.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>API</h3>
  <p>Submit a job using a preset by name:</p>
  <pre><code>curl -X POST https://controller/api/v1/jobs \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;
    "source_id": "src_abc123",
    "pipeline": &#123;
      "type": "preset",
      "preset": "1080p-x265-quality"
    &#125;,
    "output": &#123;
      "path": "/mnt/output/&#123;source_name&#125;.mkv"
    &#125;
  &#125;'</code></pre>

  <p>List all available presets:</p>
  <pre><code>curl https://controller/api/v1/presets \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY"</code></pre>

  <p>Create a custom preset:</p>
  <pre><code>curl -X POST https://controller/api/v1/presets \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;
    "name": "my-720p-h264",
    "description": "720p H.264 for tablet streaming",
    "video": &#123;
      "codec": "libx264",
      "crf": 23,
      "preset": "medium",
      "profile": "main",
      "level": "3.1",
      "scale": "1280:720"
    &#125;,
    "audio": &#123;
      "codec": "aac",
      "bitrate": "128k",
      "channels": 2
    &#125;,
    "container": "mp4"
  &#125;'</code></pre>

  <h2>Cost Estimation</h2>
  <p>
    Before submitting a job, you can request a cost estimate that returns predicted encode time, agent-hours, and (if cloud agents are configured) estimated cloud spend. The estimate is based on historical job metrics for the same preset and source duration/resolution combination.
  </p>
  <pre><code>curl -X POST https://controller/api/v1/estimate \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;
    "source_id": "src_abc123",
    "pipeline": &#123;
      "type": "preset",
      "preset": "4k-hdr10-quality"
    &#125;
  &#125;'

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
&#123;
  "estimated_duration_seconds": 7420,
  "estimated_agent_hours": 2.06,
  "estimated_cloud_cost_usd": 0.412,
  "confidence": "high",
  "based_on_samples": 34
&#125;</code></pre>
  <p>
    Confidence levels are <code>high</code> (&gt;20 historical samples), <code>medium</code> (5–20 samples), or <code>low</code> (&lt;5 samples). Low-confidence estimates have wider error margins and should be treated as rough guides only.
  </p>
